## 🏗️ Mini Project — Replace the In-Memory Slice

Take your book API from Module 4 (the one using `[]Book` in memory). Replace it entirely:
- Run the migration to create the real `books` table
- Wire up `BookRepository` with the real `*sql.DB`
- Every handler (`GET /books`, `GET /books/{id}`, `POST /books`, `DELETE /books/{id}`) now hits PostgreSQL
- `ErrNoRows` → 404, real errors → 500
- Test every endpoint with curl — data must persist between server restarts

That's the sign it's working: kill the server, restart it, hit `GET /books` — your data is still there.

